title: For Sale:  SOLD!! Thanks for looking!  Chinese SKS Rifle, 7.62x39mm, All Matching #'s!, ORIGINAL! Exc. Cond.!
location: Springfield, Branson West, Branson areas, Springfield, Missouri
postcontent: SOLD!! THANKS FOR LOOKING!  Up for sale is a Chinese Type 56 SKS Rifle. Caliber is 7.62x39mm, the same ammo used in the AK-47. For those that are familiar with the SKS, and SKS Collectors, this rifle was manufactured at Chinese State Arsenal 0129. Left side of the receiver shows the three Chinese characters that translate to "Type 56", 0129, and then the Serial Number: 211195 D. The rear of the left side of receiver shows the usual importer info: "SKS 7.62x39 Norinco China POLY U.S.A. ATL. GA." No other markings on the right side of the receiver or barrel. All Serial Numbered parts are stamped, not EP'd. I would like to say that the bluing is 100%, but after 25-35 years, surely it has faded a little. The stock has some dings and scratches from that crazy way they shipped them over here. But nothing major, at all. I really like the grain of the wood in this stock. Rifle comes with the Cleaning Kit, (in buttstock), Cleaning Rod, Sling, Bayonet, and Owners Manual. I'll even throw in a few GOOD stripper clips, not the cheapo ones that don't work well. As far as identifying aspects of the various parts of the rifle: It has the Spike Bayonet, all forged/milled parts and receiver as far as I can tell. No cast/milled parts. Side-mount for the sling on the buttstock, which I thought was interesting with a pinned barrel receiver and late model Bolt Carrier. There are three letters stamped into the buttstock directly behind the side-mount sling hardware. It may be a previous Owner's initials, I don't know. They are small, neatly done, and discreet. I have owned this SKS since 2005 and never fired a round through it. I don't know if it's been fired or not. If it has been fired, it was VERY FEW rounds. The Bolt still has cosmoline inside with the Firing Pin and is sluggish to move. So, I know it was never completely disassembled and cleaned properly for firing condition. This is extremely important on the SKS! If the new Buyer of this SKS has not performed this removal and replacement before, I can show the procedure to him or her at the time of the sale. Terms: Cash Only. Face to Face preferred. I can meet in the Springfield, Ozark, Branson West, and Branson areas. Other close areas can be considered. Price does NOT include any shipping costs or transfer fees. I can ship, but all shipping and transfer fees to be paid by Buyer. If Buyer requests shipping, I require a Postal Money Order and will ship via UPS and supply Buyer with a Tracking Number. My ZIP Code is 65737, if you'd like to estimate shipping costs to you. title: For Sale:  Troy Industries fixed rear BattleSight
postcontent:
Troy Industries fixed rear BattleSight

Continuous Zero Fixed Rear Battle Sight For Improved Accuracy & Durability

Tactical backup sight is always deployed, so there’s absolutely no delay, no fumbling when you need to transition from the primary optic. Troy designed this sight to be simple, rugged, and reliable—and it takes up only 1-1/8" of rail space. Precision machined from solid aluminum, with plenty of metal on the protective “ears” around the two-position aperture. All edges and corners are rounded, and there are no protruding knobs or levers to catch on brush, clothing, or other equipment. Rear of the base is undercut to provide clearance for access to the charging handle. Same-plane aperture flips easily between .190" and .070" diameter peeps, just like the Folding Rear Battle Sight. Windage adjustable in ½ MOA clicks using a coin in the slot of the flush A1-style detent-locking adjustment wheel. Clamps to any Picatinny rail; installs with a standard flathead screwdriver.

In very good condition. Minor installation marks. $64.99 at Brownells but not in stock. $50 shipped to lower 48 states.
